Accepted an invitation from the Australian Grand Prix Corporation, for myself and my son to attend the 2014 Formula 1 Rolex Australian Grand Prix on Sunday 16 March 2014. Two Grand Prix tickets and hospitality for my son and I were provided.

I accepted an invitation from CUB, for myself and my wife, Maureen, to attend the 2014 AFL Anzac Day Game between Collingwood & Essendon on Friday 25 April 2014 at the MCG. Two tickets and hospitality for my wife and I were provided.

I accepted an invitation from Credit Suisse, for both myself and my Senior Adviser, Angus Barker to attend a Hong Kong Rugby Sevens Game on Sunday 30 March 2014. Both the tickets and hospitality were provided.

On 10 May 2014, I was boarding a Qantas Flight from Dubai to Melbourne (QF10), I was informed by the flight attendant that a flight upgrade from Business Class to First class had been arranged for myself and Chief of Staff, Zoe McKenzie.

Accepted an invitation from Geelong Cats, for both myself and my wife to attend the Geelong Cats v North Melbourne at Simonds Stadium on Friday 23 May 2014. Both the tickets and hospitality were provided.
Accepted an invitation from the AFL Commission, for myself and my wife, Maureen, at the AFL Grand Final & luncheon on 27 September 2014 at the MCG.

Accepted an invitation from the Melbourne Football Club, for myself and my wife, Maureen, at attend the Melbourne Demons v Geelong Cats AFL game on 12 July 2014 at the MCG. Tickets and hospitality for my wife and I were provided.
Accepted an offer of hospitality & incidentals from the Singapore MFA. This consisted of 2 night's accommodation in a Junior Suite at the Shangri La Hotel in Singapore.
Accepted an offer of complimentary upgrade from a Standard room to a Suite by the St Regis Hotel in Beijing.
Accepted an offer of complimentary upgrade from a Standard room to a Club room by the Intercontinental Hotel Madrid.
